    &lt;Title&gt;Excellent care&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;We arrived to Ward 8 (children's ward) from Bolton A &amp;amp; E in the early hours of Sunday morning. It was unfortunate that we had to be transferred due to the sharing of ENT services across Bolton and Preston and our arrival hadn't been communicated to the ward however we were made to feel very comfortable and we had a bed very quickly despite not being being told we were arriving. The assessment took some time but once that had taken place, we were taken to a side room with space for us both to sleep. The nurses taking care of us on the night shift put us at ease and gave us great care, as did the day time staff. The ward was very clean and the auxiliary staff were just as attentive and friendly. An excellent job in challenging circumstances and we are very grateful for the great job, thank you.  &lt;/CommentText&gt;
